---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout>
  <main class="app-container pt-32 md:pt-40 pb-14 md:pb-20">
    <section class="max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold leading-none">
        About Me
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-8 text-xl leading-relaxed">
        I’m James Littlewood, a Technical Data Analyst based in Reading, Berkshire.
        I work with product data, structured validation, categorisation, taxonomy
        application, SQL analysis and stakeholder communication, with a focus on
        accurate eCommerce product data delivery across BAU operations, client
        implementation activity and SLA-driven workflows.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-relaxed">
        I’m currently developing my skills in SQL, Excel, Tableau, Python, Git,
        Shell, Snowflake fundamentals, PostgreSQL, Docker and remote development
        workflows. Alongside my day-to-day role, I maintain a personal Ubuntu-based
        development environment using PostgreSQL, Docker, VS Code Remote SSH and
        DBeaver to practise database administration, containerised workflows and
        hands-on technical development.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="section-title">Core Skills</h2>

      <div class="mt-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data and Reporting</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            Excel, Google Sheets, SQL, PostgreSQL, Snowflake fundamentals,
            Tableau, data cleaning and reporting support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Product and Operations Data</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            Product data validation, categorisation, taxonomy application,
            attribute QA, exception handling, quality checks and SLA-driven delivery.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Analysis Concepts</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            Joining and structuring data, data literacy, data modelling fundamentals,
            basic statistical thinking, dashboard design and communicating insights clearly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Technical Tools</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            Python fundamentals, pandas, regex, Git, Shell, Docker concepts,
            DBeaver and VS Code.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="section-title">Professional Experience</h2>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-10">
        <article>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Technical Data Analyst — Profitero</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-lg opacity-80">August 2025 – Present</p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            In my current role, I manage product data tasks across assigned clients,
            markets and implementation activity, supporting both day-to-day operations
            and new setup work.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            My work includes maintaining and validating product identifiers, titles,
            brands, manufacturers, pack sizes and structured attributes to help ensure
            accurate product records. I also apply client-specific taxonomies,
            categorisation rules and data standards across multiple retailers and markets.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I use Excel and structured validation checks to review product data at scale,
            identify inconsistencies, support exception handling and improve accuracy
            across operational workflows. I also track workload in JIRA and internal tools,
            monitor progress against SLAs, and communicate blockers, dependencies and risks.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Team Lead Temporary Secondment — Apple</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-lg opacity-80">October 2021 – April 2022</p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            During my temporary secondment as Team Lead, I supported a multifunctional team
            in a fast-paced technical retail environment, balancing customer escalations,
            operational priorities and service standards.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I monitored performance indicators and operational patterns to improve customer
            flow, reduce wait times and support decision-making. I also helped identify
            coaching opportunities, support training, and maintain consistency and service
            quality across the team.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Technical Expert / Expert — Apple</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-lg opacity-80">April 2015 – June 2022</p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            In my Apple technical roles, I handled troubleshooting, diagnostics and repair
            workflows while working to appointment schedules and service expectations.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            This involved structured problem-solving, evidence gathering, pattern recognition,
            accurate service notes and clear communication with customers and colleagues.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="section-title">Projects and Professional Development</h2>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-10">
        <article>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Analytics Course — The Curious Academy</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-lg opacity-80">16-week programme | May 2025 – July 2025</p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            As part of my data analytics training, I worked on practical projects using
            PostgreSQL and Tableau. I analysed approximately 24 million Chicago bike share
            records in PostgreSQL to identify usage patterns, behavioural differences and
            seasonality by member type.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I also investigated around 350,000 Land Registry records for RG postcode house
            prices, using PostgreSQL for analysis and Tableau to present findings clearly.
            Another project involved creating a Tableau dashboard analysing the performance
            of the NHL team Anaheim Ducks in comparison with other NHL teams.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Personal Projects and Learning</h3>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I continue to build practical skills through DataCamp learning, personal projects
            and independent technical experimentation. My current focus areas include SQL,
            Excel, data analysis, visualisation, Tableau dashboard development, Snowflake,
            data modelling fundamentals, Python basics, statistics, data literacy and
            communicating insights.
          </p>

          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
            I also use a personal Ubuntu-based mini-server environment to build experience
            with PostgreSQL, Docker, VS Code Remote SSH, DBeaver and remote development workflows.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="section-title">Education and Certifications</h2>

      <ul class="mt-6 list-disc list-inside text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-2">
        <li>BSc (Hons) Audio Engineering and Music Production, SAE Institute / Middlesex University — 2:1</li>
        <li>Apple iOS / Mac Certified Technician</li>
        <li>The Curious Academy — Data Analysis Certification</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-16 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="section-title">Contact</h2>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        You can view my portfolio and projects through this website, or visit my
        DataCamp portfolio:
      </p>

      <a
        href="https://www.datacamp.com/portfolio/jameslittlewood"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-block mt-4 text-lg underline"
      >
        datacamp.com/portfolio/jameslittlewood
      </a>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>